title: Sea Level Anomaly Prediction
description: Extracted key sea level anomaly (SLA) metrics from 20 years of tide gauge data (7,300+ files) for 12 East Coast stations. Developed a Random Forest Classifier achieving 97.7% test accuracy, predicting 10 years of future anomalies to improve coastal flood preparedness and proactive resource allocation.

title: U.S. Power Outage Analysis
description: Analyzed 1,534 power outages over 15+ years, uncovering trends in weather, population density, and state-level factors. Improved outage duration prediction by 25% through feature engineering, data preprocessing, ML models, and fairness analysis.

title: SharpKids

Personalized live healthcare recommendations for children via ArcGIS geospatial tracking and data monetization strategies. Won 2nd Place out of  60+ Teams and 200+ Participants at Big Data Hackathon 2024 at SDSU.
